rComments: Lectures are very content heavy and not much info on her slides. Tutorials are fun because they are in kitchens and you actually cook. She's kind of rude when you ask her questions though. Fully regret taking this class

Good professor at utsc, overall interesting information. she is obviously a historian who understands what she is talking about. got a regrade on my paper that a t.a. murdered me for, very helpful and approachable. i would take any of her classes again.

Attendance is definitely mandatory. Prof. has a thick french accent so it is difficult to understand her at first, but it gets easier and she is very thorough in her lectures. Course was midterm, final, 2-part assignment and tut. participation. Very possible to get an A.
Begin is an okay prof when it comes to delivering lectures. Her keywords were especially helpful for the midterm and exam. Overall though I found her a bit snooty and unapproachable.
